            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "If you are genuinely concerned about your child's overall development then please stay away from this school. My two kids go to this school and they are having a really bad experience and as soon as this session ends I'll change the school.\nThere is very poor management in school. We are always confused about what books to send to school, which activities are happening. And they make kids wait to play sports but never let them do it properly. Extra curriculars are just in their marketing materials, teachers are least bothered about that. My children are really interested in learning more but they get least support. Just today as I am writing this review I learnt that my child was not allowed to do skating in school coz he was unable to put on the skating kit on his own. It was supposed to be his first day and they expect little kids to be expert right out on their own. This does it.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
